add spacing to text:
Tailwind only supports specific spacing scale values, not really sure what makes it work or not, py seems to cap out at 12 while mb can do roughly 20

| Utility | Meaning                 |
| ------- | ----------------------- |
| `m-*`   | margin on **all** sides |
| `mt-*`  | margin-top              |
| `mb-*`  | margin-bottom           |
| `ml-*`  | margin-left             |
| `mr-*`  | margin-right            |
| `mx-*`  | left + right            |
| `my-*`  | top + bottom            |

| Utility | Meaning                  |
| ------- | ------------------------ |
| `p-*`   | padding on **all** sides |
| `pt-*`  | padding-top              |
| `pb-*`  | padding-bottom           |
| `pl-*`  | padding-left             |
| `pr-*`  | padding-right            |
| `px-*`  | left + right             |
| `py-*`  | top + bottom             |





color specific text:
<h4 class="text-[3em] mb-2 text-[#b91c1c]">
  You Aren’t Supposed to Be Here.
</h4>
text-[3em] → Custom font size of 3em (Tailwind’s arbitrary value syntax).
mb-2 → Margin-bottom roughly equal to 0.5em. Tailwind has fixed spacing scales; mb-2 is usually 0.5rem, close enough. You can also do mb-[0.5em] if you want exact.
text-[#b91c1c] → Sets the text color to that exact blood-red hex.




add bullet points to <ul> in tailwind
you need to add this class
example: <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
list-disc → shows bullets
list-decimal → shows numbers
list-inside → bullets inside padding
space-y-2 → vertical spacing between items



primary button:
<a href="/" 
   class="inline-block bg-indigo-600 text-white font-semibold py-3 px-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg 
          hover:bg-indigo-500 hover:translate-y-[-2px] transition-transform transition-colors">
  Return Home
</a>
Base classes
  inline-block → Makes the <a> behave like a block-level element horizontally sized to its content, so padding and margin work like a button.
  bg-indigo-600 → Sets the button’s background color (Indigo 600 from Tailwind’s color palette).
  text-white → Makes the text white.
  font-semibold → Semi-bold font weight for emphasis.
  py-3 px-6 → Vertical (py-3) and horizontal (px-6) padding to make it look like a proper button.
  rounded-lg → Gives the corners a large rounded radius.
  shadow-lg → Adds a prominent drop shadow for depth and separation from the background.
Hover / interactive classes
  hover:bg-indigo-500 → Changes background color slightly on hover for visual feedback.
  hover:translate-y-[-2px] → Moves the button up 2px when hovered, giving a subtle “lift” effect.
Transition / animation classes
  transition-transform → Smoothly animates any transform changes (like translate-y).
  transition-colors → Smoothly animates color changes (like bg-indigo-600 → bg-indigo-500).
